# TypeScript & React

## Imports and paths

- Use `@/` alias for `src/` (e.g. `@/features/invites/invite-links`).

## Domain logic

- Put **pure, testable logic** in `src/features/` (no React, no DOM).
- Colocate feature modules by domain (`invites/`, `auth/`).
- Unit-test features from `tests/unit/`.

## Environment

- Validate env via Zod in `src/lib/env.ts`; do not read `process.env` ad hoc in components.

```typescript
// Bad — scattered env access
const url = process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL;

// Good — centralized schema
import { getEnv } from "@/lib/env";
const { NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_URL } = getEnv();
```

## UI copy

- User-facing strings in **Turkish** (invite pages, marketing).
- UI work: follow `design-system/halisaha/MASTER.md` brand overrides; tokens in `src/styles/tokens.css`.

## Error handling

- No empty `catch` blocks; handle or rethrow with context.

## Components

- Prefer functional components and named exports for feature modules.
- Keep components focused; extract hooks only when logic is reused.
